WEBVTT

00:00:00.433 --> 00:00:03.570
Within 60 days of the end of the appraisal period,

00:00:03.636 --> 00:00:06.473
the Employee will receive his or her written or otherwise

00:00:06.539 --> 00:00:08.808
documented rating of record.

00:00:08.875 --> 00:00:11.611
There is an exception for an Employee who has less than 90

00:00:11.678 --> 00:00:14.180
days of employment with the Department.

00:00:14.247 --> 00:00:17.550
The time frame for the rating of record may be extended to allow

00:00:17.617 --> 00:00:21.321
the Employee 90 days to perform according to his or her

00:00:21.388 --> 00:00:24.557
appraisal plan before being evaluated.

00:00:24.624 --> 00:00:27.560
There is also a provision for an employee who changes his or her

00:00:27.627 --> 00:00:32.365
position during the last 90 days of the appraisal period.

00:00:32.432 --> 00:00:36.269
The new Rater can either extend the rating period or concur with

00:00:36.336 --> 00:00:39.506
the previously issued performance rating for this Employee.


